# Slash commands (type `/` in chat)

| Command | Action |
|---------|--------|
| `/push` | Commit current progress with a readable English message, then push (usually `dev` → `origin/dev`) |
| `/pack` | Run `bash scripts/package.sh` → `dist/Ask_AI_Plugin_vX.Y.Z.zip` |
| `/version-up` | Bump version per `.cursor/rules/version-update.mdc` |

When the user invokes one of these (via slash command or by saying the same intent), follow the matching prompt in `.cursor/commands/<name>.md` exactly.

## Commit message style for `/push`

Use clear English with connecting words (not telegraphic keyword stacks), e.g. “Add … after …”, “Fix … when …”.

## Defaults

- Push target: current branch’s upstream; if on `dev`, push to `origin/dev`.
- Never force-push unless the user explicitly asks.
- `/version-up` does not commit or pack unless combined with `/push` / `/pack`.
